    <who name="Jason Tibbitts">tibbs</who>
    <bug_when>2016-06-23 14:03:30 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>This may be a dumb request, but is there any possibility you&apos;d consider splitting out just /usr/bin/resize and its manpage to a subpackage?

Basically, resize is super useful for things like a serial console connection.  Which is exactly the situation where you probably don&apos;t have X installed.

/usr/bin/resize has no X dependencies.  Sometimes I just copy the binary over, but it would be really nice to just install xterm-resize.  Other uses would see no change given the proper dependency.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
